Class MissDeadlineInfo

java.lang.Object
ResultSet.MissDeadlineInfo
public class MissDeadlineInfo extends Object
Encapsulates information about a missed deadline detected during the simulation.

This object stores the time of the deadline miss (in the simulator's internal time units), the Job that missed its deadline, and the Task that the job belongs to. The stored time is converted to wall-clock/simulated units by getMissTime() which divides the internal time by magnificationFactor from RTSimulator.Definition.

Author:
ShiuJia

      Creates an empty MissDeadlineInfo with default values.

    • MissDeadlineInfo

      public MissDeadlineInfo(int t, Job j)
      Creates a MissDeadlineInfo for a specific deadline miss event.
      Parameters:
      t - the miss time in the simulator's internal time units (ticks)
      j - the Job that missed its deadline; if non-null, the parent Task is captured via j.getParentTask()

    • getMissTime

      public double getMissTime()
      Returns the recorded miss time converted from internal time units.

      The stored missTime is divided by magnificationFactor (from RTSimulator.Definition) to produce the returned value.

      Returns:
      the miss time adjusted by magnificationFactor
